1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
 Well, we all daydream, every single one of us.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,000
 And so one recurring daydream that I used to have is that I was rich,

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:19,000
 successful, had a big house or maybe multiple homes, cars,

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:26,000
 I'm surrounded by people, and I'm feeling like I've made it.

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:35,000
 I've arrived, I've proven myself.

6
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:39,000
 And if I'm really honest, that's not where the daydreaming stopped,

7
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,000
 it actually even went further.

8
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:47,000
 It also involved me talking to some people who maybe didn't believe in me

9
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
 and telling them how amazing and what amazing things I accomplished

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:55,000
 or certain people for whatever reason that I want them to be there,

11
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,000
 that they also overhear or see whatever I have to say.

12
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,000
 And then suddenly, while I'm feeling good about myself,

13
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:09,000
 I snap out of my daydream, it's over and I'm back to reality.

14
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:12,000
 Anyone with me?

15
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,000
 Okay, a few, thank you.

16
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,000
 I think there's more, but I appreciate your daydreaming,

17
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
 you shared it with me.

18
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:23,000
 But I actually want us to think about what do you daydream about right now?

19
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:27,000
 And what recurring theme is there?

20
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:34,000
 Actually, take a moment to think about this.

21
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
 Alright, I just trust you know what you daydream about,

22
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
 so you could get it quite quickly.

23
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:47,000
 Well, our daydreams, they're actually not random.

24
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:52,000
 Now, some of them are, I'm sure some daydreams are totally random.

25
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:55,000
 But the ones that are recurring,

26
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:01,000
 they actually speak of a longing that is inside of our heart.

27
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:06,000
 They speak of something where we think that if this will happen,

28
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:11,000
 then I'm going to be fulfilled, then I will feel good,

29
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,000
 then I will experience joy in my life.

30
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:18,000
 And we dream of relationships,

31
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:22,000
 we dream of, like I said, success and material things,

32
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:26,000
 like an amazing car.

33
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
 But here's another question for you.

34
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:34,000
 If your daydream would be fulfilled,

35
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:38,000
 like if actually everything you daydream about would happen,

36
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:43,000
 would this longing in your heart still be there?

37
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:47,000
 Or would it be satisfied?

38
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:52,000
 And I believe that while there is satisfaction in some of those things,

39
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,000
 let's be honest,

40
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:58,000
 I still think that that longing in your heart would still be there.

41
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:02,000
 I think it would not fully go away.

42
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:06,000
 And so what I want to do with you today is I want to explore with you a question.

43
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:11,000
 Where do we find satisfaction for our deepest longings?

44
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,000
 You know, where do we go?

45
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
 And how do we receive that?

46
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
 Like, what are we supposed to do?

47
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:26,000
 And so today we're continuing in our I Am Christmas Advent Sermon series,

48
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:30,000
 where we are going through parts of the Gospel of John.

49
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:37,000
 The Gospel of John doesn't have a birth narrative like Matthew and Luke from Jesus,

50
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,000
 so it doesn't tell the story of how Jesus was born.

51
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:45,000
 Instead, it has a theological opening to the book that the Word became flesh

52
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,000
 and made its dwelling among us.

53
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:51,000
 So Jesus was born and dwelt among us.

54
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
 And then throughout the Gospel, there are these I Am statements.

55
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:59,000
 There's actually seven of them, and we're looking at five during this series.

56
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:04,000
 And in these I Am statements, Jesus declaring who he is, why he has come,

57
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
 what he wants us to know and understand about him.

58
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,000
 And so as we're going through Christmas, you want to look and understand,

59
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,000
 why do we celebrate Christmas? Why did he come?

60
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,000
 And so that's what we're doing in this series.

61
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,000
 I hope so far it's been helpful for you.

62
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,000
 I've been enjoying it.

63
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,000
 But I want to set the context for today's passage.

64
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
 We're in John chapter 6.

65
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:31,000
 Now, Jesus has just done this absolutely incredible miracle.

66
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:35,000
 There was 5,000 people, or actually probably more like 20,000 people,

67
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,000
 because when the Bible talks about 5,000 people,

68
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,000
 it just lists the head of the households.

69
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:45,000
 And so there was probably 20,000 people out in the wilderness,

70
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,000
 and they have no food.

71
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
 And Jesus takes a little bit of bread, takes a little bit of fish,

72
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,000
 and he multiplies it.

73
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
 I mean, an incredible miracle.

74
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,000
 Unbelievable. Amazing.

75
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,000
 And people are amazed.

76
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:02,000
 They're actually amazed so much so that they want to force Jesus to be king

77
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,000
 because they want him to make more bread for them.

78
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,000
 And so Jesus withdraws. He goes to the mountain.

79
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:09,000
 His disciples, they end up taking a ship to Capernaum,

80
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,000
 but Jesus stays back.

81
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
 Then another miracle occurs.

82
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,000
 Jesus walks on water, and he actually goes to Capernaum.

83
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,000
 So there's two miracles within a short period of time.

84
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,000
 And in Capernaum, so he's there.

85
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:27,000
 The next day, the people wake up, and they try to find, "Where's Jesus?

86
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,000
 Where did he go? We're in the middle of nowhere."

87
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,000
 They slept there.

88
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,000
 And then boats from Tiberius arrive.

89
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,000
 They get into the boat.

90
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,000
 They're searching for Jesus.

91
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,000
 They go to Capernaum, and they find him.

92
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,000
 And that's where we're going to pick things up.

93
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,000
 So we're in John 6, verse 25.

94
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:45,000
 It says this, "When they found him on the other side of the lake,

95
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,000
 they asked him, 'Rabbi, when did you get here?'

96
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:51,000
 Jesus answered, 'Very truly I tell you,

97
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:55,000
 you are looking for me not because you saw the signs I performed,

98
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,000
 but because you ate the loaves and had your fill.

99
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:01,000
 Do not work for the food that spoils,

100
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,000
 but for food that endures the eternal life,

101
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
 which the Son of Man will give you.

102
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:12,000
 For on him God the Father has placed a seal of approval.'

103
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:17,000
 Then they asked him, 'What must we do to do the works God requires?'

104
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:22,000
 Jesus answered, 'The work of God is this, to believe in the one he has sent.'

105
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,000
 So they asked him, 'What sign then will you give

106
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:29,000
 that we may see it and believe in you?

107
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,000
 What will you do?'

108
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,000
 Our answer is, 'Eat the manna in the wilderness.'

109
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,000
 As it is written, 'He gave them bread from heaven to eat.'

110
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:40,000
 Jesus said to them, 'Very truly I tell you,

111
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
 it is not Moses who has given you the bread from heaven,

112
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:48,000
 but it was my Father who gives you the true bread from heaven.

113
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,000
 For the bread of God is the bread that comes down from heaven

114
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,000
 and gives life to the world.'

115
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:58,000
 'Sir,' they said, 'always give us this bread.'

116
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:02,000
 Then Jesus declared, 'I am the bread of life.

117
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,000
 Whoever comes to me will never go hungry,

118
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:11,000
 and whoever believes in me will never be thirsty.'

119
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:15,000
 So today the 'I am' statement that we're unpacking is

120
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:19,000
 the 'I am the bread of life,'

121
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:24,000
 where Jesus is saying, 'I'm the one who satisfies these longings,'

122
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:29,000
 these things that we're trying to grab hold of when we daydream

123
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:33,000
 and we hope they're going to bring us that fulfillment.

124
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:38,000
 But what's interesting is, leading up to this declaration from Jesus,

125
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,000
 there's this dialogue back and forth.

126
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,000
 You see it as I was reading.

127
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
 There's all these questions that the crowd's asking Jesus,

128
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:49,000
 and he patiently engages all these questions.

129
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:55,000
 In the pastures that we see from the crowd that's asking these questions,

130
00:07:55,000 --> 00:08:00,000
 we actually see three ways of relating to Jesus

131
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:07,000
 that keep us from receiving the fullness, the joy,

132
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:12,000
 the contentment that Jesus actually wants to give us.

133
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,000
 So what I want to do with you,

134
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:18,000
 I want to look at these three ways of how we relate to Jesus

135
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,000
 that kind of undermine that,

136
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:25,000
 and then of course also look at how we receive this life that Jesus has to offer.

137
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:28,000
 So let's look at the first one.

138
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,000
 When the crowd finds Jesus in Capernaum, and I love this,

139
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:34,000
 they're like, 'Hey, Rabbi, when did you get here?'

140
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:40,000
 It's like, 'Hey, what's up? Small talk, yeah, nice weather.'

141
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:44,000
 And then Jesus, and I love Jesus with this when I read the Gospels,

142
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:47,000
 he doesn't answer that question.

143
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,000
 He doesn't tell them when he got there.

144
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,000
 'I got here at 3 p.m. or a.m. at night.'

145
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,000
 He doesn't do that, but he cuts right through it

146
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,000
 because he knows why they're there, and he says this.

147
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:01,000
 He says, 'Very truly I tell you, you are looking for me

148
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,000
 not because you saw the signs I performed,

149
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:08,000
 but because you ate the loaves and you had your fill.'

150
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:14,000
 So Jesus discerns, 'They're talking to me because they want more bread.'

151
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:23,000
 But what's incredible is they actually are missing what the sign points to,

152
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,000
 this miracle that Jesus said points to.

153
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:30,000
 This multiplying of bread points to that Jesus is the Messiah,

154
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:33,000
 that he's God with us, but they're not seeing that.

155
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,000
 What they're seeing is dollar signs.

156
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:40,000
 'He can make some bread, and we can make some money,

157
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,000
 and it's going to be great.'

158
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 Now, one thing we have to realize is at the time

159
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:52,000
 that people spent 80% of their income on food.

160
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,000
 Just think of your paycheck right now.

161
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:59,000
 Take 80% away from that, and think of that that was needed

162
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:03,000
 just to put food on the table, just to survive.

163
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:07,000
 Now, for some of us, that actually might be our reality even here.

164
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:10,000
 But there are quite a few where that's not the case,

165
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:14,000
 where the money we spend on food is much smaller.

166
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:17,000
 So we can understand why this is a huge deal

167
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:23,000
 that Jesus has multiplied and made all this bread.

168
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,000
 This is a big deal.

169
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:28,000
 So they're like, 'All right, Jesus, you're going to make this bread.

170
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:34,000
 We're all going to be able to save all this 80% that we need to spend on food.

171
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:38,000
 And then after we save a little bit, we can buy some chickens.

172
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,000
 And then we can buy some lambs.

173
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,000
 We can buy a field, and we can get this business going.

174
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:45,000
 It's going to be amazing.'

175
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:49,000
 But you know what the problem here is?

176
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,000
 That the people are coming to Jesus

177
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:56,000
 because they want to fulfill their own agenda.

178
00:10:56,000 --> 00:11:00,000
 They're actually not interested or care about who Jesus is.

179
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:04,000
 They're just coming to Jesus with their own plans.

180
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,000
 Now, actually, wanting to start a business, there's nothing wrong with that.

181
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,000
 It's actually a blessing.

182
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,000
 It's a good thing.

183
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:13,000
 And wanting sheep and wanting chickens, that's okay.

184
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,000
 We can actually bring those things to Jesus.

185
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:23,000
 But the problem is that when we only approach Jesus

186
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:28,000
 with the purpose of having him help us achieve our goals

187
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:31,000
 and accomplish our own ends,

188
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:34,000
 then we miss out on what Jesus truly has to offer,

189
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:38,000
 which is a life-transforming relationship with him.

190
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:46,000
 So Jesus calls out the crowd's treatment of him in this.

191
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:50,000
 And he does that with you and me as well.

192
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,000
 Now, I don't know if you've ever been used

193
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:56,000
 where somebody just had an agenda and didn't care about you.

194
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 I've experienced that.

195
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,000
 I was in university.

196
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:04,000
 A friend was getting married in Alaska.

197
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,000
 He was Alaskan.

198
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,000
 So I flew there for the wedding, hung out with a group of people.

199
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
 We had a good time.

200
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,000
 Then I went back to university, Portland area.

201
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:15,000
 A few months later, I hear from one of the guys, "Hey, Tim.

202
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,000
 Hey, I'm flying down with my father-in-law on a private plane.

203
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,000
 We're going to land close to you.

204
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:24,000
 I would love to talk to you about a business idea.

205
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,000
 Would you have time to meet up?"

206
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,000
 And I have to admit, I was flattered.

207
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,000
 Ooh, private plane.

208
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,000
 You're flying to visit me.

209
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,000
 What business idea is this?

210
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,000
 Is this what I've been waiting for and dreaming for

211
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:39,000
 to make my daydream come true?

212
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:42,000
 So I meet up with him.

213
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,000
 He tells me about this business, and he gives me some samples.

214
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,000
 I'm like, "Oh, great."

215
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
 He's like, "Think about it. I'll come back in a week."

216
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,000
 I was like, "Okay, sounds good."

217
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,000
 So I'm trying to sort out what I make of this.

218
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:56,000
 So I talked to a business professor that I was studying under.

219
00:12:56,000 --> 00:13:00,000
 She's like, "Tim, this is a permit scheme."

220
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,000
 So if you're not familiar with a permit scheme,

221
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,000
 it's like basically you buy stuff,

222
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,000
 and then you try to get other people to buy stuff,

223
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,000
 and then they try to get people to buy stuff,

224
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,000
 and every time the permit expands, there's a kickback up to you.

225
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:15,000
 But a lot of times, most people don't make money with that.

226
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,000
 They just get stuck with a bunch of products that they never sell.

227
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,000
 Their house.

228
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:22,000
 And so the friend comes back, and he tells me,

229
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,000
 "So, do you want to join in?"

230
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:27,000
 I was like, "No, I decided not to."

231
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,000
 And then he asked me for the samples back,

232
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:32,000
 and I was like, "Oh, I thought they were free. Okay, sure, here you go."

233
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:36,000
 He was kind of angry and cold, and just then left.

234
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,000
 I never heard from him again.

235
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:43,000
 So all he cared about was getting his business going,

236
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:46,000
 but he didn't care about me in any way or form.

237
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:49,000
 And we kind of do that to Jesus.

238
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:53,000
 We come to Jesus that he can fulfill our agenda,

239
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:56,000
 that he can make our dreams come true.

240
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:00,000
 And like I said, we can actually bring things that we desire to Jesus.

241
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:03,000
 We don't have to be embarrassed to ask Jesus.

242
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:07,000
 Some Christian environments, you get scolded for coming to Jesus

243
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:11,000
 and asking for things, but if you miss the person,

244
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:15,000
 if you don't care about who Jesus is, you're missing all of it.

245
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:19,000
 So that's the first way of relating to Jesus that the crowd does.

246
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:23,000
 They're there, they just want bread, they don't care about anything else.

247
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:26,000
 And when you do that, you miss out on what Jesus has to offer

248
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:30,000
 and what he wants to give you, which is a life-transforming relationship.

249
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
 So that's the first thing.

250
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:36,000
 Let's go to the next one.

251
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:40,000
 So Jesus is still responding to the, "Hey, when did you get here?" question.

252
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,000
 We're still on that. I haven't gotten very far.

253
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:47,000
 Verse 27, he says this.

254
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:51,000
 "Do not work for food that spoils, but for food that endures eternal life,

255
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:54,000
 which the Son of Man will give you.

256
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:58,000
 For on him God the Father has placed a seal of approval."

257
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:07,000
 So Jesus is telling the crowd, "Stop chasing and working for these material things."

258
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:11,000
 You know, it's stuff that spoils, it's stuff that doesn't deliver.

259
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:16,000
 It just maybe satisfies a little bit, but then you have to do it all over again.

260
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:22,000
 Instead, get this life that I have to offer.

261
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:27,000
 Receive that, go after that, chase that.

262
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:33,000
 Now, again, it doesn't mean we're not supposed to work and put food on the table.

263
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,000
 Obviously, we need to do that, we should do that.

264
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:41,000
 That honors God, we're created to be people who work and do creative things.

265
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:45,000
 But if we think that the material things that we're working for,

266
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:50,000
 that they're somehow going to fill our hearts and make us whole,

267
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:58,000
 and make us worthy, and make us good or joyful,

268
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:03,000
 then if that's what we think, and we're chasing after that,

269
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,000
 and we're trying to achieve that,

270
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:11,000
 we're actually putting our hope in a false thing.

271
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:15,000
 And I think we all know that because we all look, we all do that.

272
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:21,000
 Everyone, pastors, everyone, we think that these things,

273
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,000
 that they're going to make us content, that they're going to make us feel good.

274
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:26,000
 And it kind of usually goes like this.

275
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:30,000
 We say to ourselves, "I know what's going to make me happy.

276
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:35,000
 I know what's going to make me feel good, feel fulfilled, feel whole.

277
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:38,000
 It's if I have this.

278
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:41,000
 And then once I have this, then I'm going to be okay.

279
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:44,000
 Then I'm going to be fine, it's going to be amazing, it's going to be great.

280
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:50,000
 My whole life is going to be turned around."

281
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,000
 Maybe it's a PlayStation 5.

282
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:58,000
 That's a little dream, right? That's pretty achievable.

283
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:01,000
 Maybe it's a flat, owning a flat in Hong Kong.

284
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:05,000
 Oh, that's expensive.

285
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:09,000
 Maybe it's that specific designer purse or dress.

286
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:12,000
 Maybe that's been sitting in your cart, your online shopping cart.

287
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:16,000
 You're just waiting to click that button.

288
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,000
 But we do that with things. I did that.

289
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:23,000
 I had friends who had these amazing leather jackets when I was a little bit younger.

290
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:26,000
 And I was like, "Man, I want this amazing leather jacket.

291
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:32,000
 If I have this, it's somehow going to make me feel good.

292
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:35,000
 And I'm going to be cool."

293
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:38,000
 Which I wasn't.

294
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:41,000
 So I bought this leather jacket, which was way too expensive.

295
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,000
 I actually couldn't afford it.

296
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,000
 So I'm struggling because I buy this leather jacket.

297
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:50,000
 Then I was scared to wear it, because it was so expensive.

298
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:53,000
 So then I only wore it a few times.

299
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:58,000
 I did enjoy it when I wore it, and it definitely did not deliver on the coolness factor.

300
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:01,000
 Total bust on that.

301
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:04,000
 Did it make me happy? Did it bring some joy?

302
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,000
 It brought some joy.

303
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,000
 But it didn't deliver on what I thought it would.

304
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:13,000
 It always falls short. It never fully delivers.

305
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,000
 But we go through these cycles.

306
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:20,000
 We pick this thing, like the leather jacket or whatever it is for you,

307
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:25,000
 and then it stirs the heart like, "Man, if I only had this, I'm going to be okay.

308
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:29,000
 I'm going to feel good. I'm going to be whole."

309
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:32,000
 And then if we're able to achieve it,

310
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:37,000
 when we actually get it, we always then start looking for something else.

311
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,000
 Eventually.

312
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:42,000
 Now, there's a lot of dreams we don't achieve, so we're still under the illusion

313
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:46,000
 that if we were to get that, it actually would make us happy.

314
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:52,000
 Like maybe being ultra successful, being part of 0.0000001%.

315
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:55,000
 Well, that's how many people achieve that, right?

316
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,000
 So it's not very many.

317
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:02,000
 Even if we were to achieve that, it still never fully delivers.

318
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:06,000
 It's a lie that we believe. We all believe it.

319
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,000
 At some point or another.

320
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:11,000
 Sometimes we're not aware of it, sometimes we're not.

321
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,000
 So Jesus is saying, "Do not work for food that spoils,

322
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:20,000
 but for food that endures to eternal life, which the Son of Man will give you."

323
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:27,000
 It's not the material things that satisfy your deep hunger.

324
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 It's Jesus.

325
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:35,000
 And Jesus is saying, "Come and receive from me the life that truly satisfies.

326
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,000
 Come receive it from me."

327
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 But let me ask you this.

328
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:45,000
 What have you been obsessing over lately?

329
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:52,000
 What is that one thing that you are convinced will finally make you content?

330
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 What has made you angry when it didn't work out?

331
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:01,000
 It's also a sign that you're looking for something to give you something.

332
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:07,000
 When it doesn't work out, you get really upset, you get really angry.

333
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:12,000
 I've experienced that anger not that long ago.

334
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:16,000
 I was trying to purchase something and it fell through.

335
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,000
 I was so angry.

336
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:20,000
 I was surprised at my emotion actually.

337
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,000
 I was like, "Whoa, where is this coming from?"

338
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,000
 So I was like processing it.

339
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:33,000
 After a while I was like, "Oh my gosh, I've made this thing an idol.

340
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:37,000
 I thought that this thing can give me something that only God can give."

341
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:40,000
 So I want to give you this definition from Tim Keller of an idol.

342
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:43,000
 I'm sorry for jumping around all over the place in my message,

343
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:47,000
 which you guys don't know, but he knows.

344
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:54,000
 So Tim Keller says this, "An idol is anything more important to you than God,

345
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:58,000
 anything that absorbs your heart and imagination more than God,

346
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:04,000
 anything you seek to give you what God can only give."

347
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:12,000
 The stuff we daydream about, that grabs our imagination,

348
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:18,000
 that we think is going to deliver.

349
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:22,000
 And Jesus says, "Don't go after that, it never fully delivers.

350
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:25,000
 Come and receive from me the life that truly satisfies."

351
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:28,000
 But let's continue to the next one.

352
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:34,000
 So Jesus challenges the crowd to work for the food that endures.

353
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:37,000
 And they pick up on the word "work." "Oh, work," he said, "work."

354
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:46,000
 So they ask someone, verse 28, "What must we do to do the work that God requires?"

355
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,000
 Essentially they're asking for a checklist.

356
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:51,000
 Tell me what to do so I can get what I want.

357
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:58,000
 So I know what to do to earn this favor with God.

358
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:02,000
 And I love how Jesus flips the script on them.

359
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:06,000
 And we can easily read over this, and I actually didn't notice what happened.

360
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:10,000
 So in verse 29 he says this, he confronts them in their thinking.

361
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:17,000
 He says, "The work of God is this, to believe in the one he has sent."

362
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,000
 They're asking, "What do we need to do?"

363
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:23,000
 And he starts talking about what God has done.

364
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:29,000
 He has already achieved so that we can just receive.

365
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:36,000
 But we're asking, "What can we do to earn this right standing with God,

366
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:39,000
 to make stuff happen in our lives?"

367
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:42,000
 And he's actually saying, "There's nothing you can do."

368
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:44,000
 It's actually part of the gospel message.

369
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:48,000
 "There's nothing you can do out of your human strength

370
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:52,000
 to get into a right relationship with God. Nothing."

371
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:55,000
 It sounds maybe kind of depressing.

372
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:59,000
 But it's the truth, because we can't earn it.

373
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,000
 But Jesus has gone to the cross.

374
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:07,000
 He has achieved forgiveness

375
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:10,000
 so that we can be brought into this relationship with God.

376
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:12,000
 We can only just receive it.

377
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:17,000
 And it's actually humbling, because we have no bargaining chips.

378
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:23,000
 We come empty-handed to God, but he loves just giving us his grace.

379
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:28,000
 All we need to do is believe and receive.

380
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:33,000
 Just come to Jesus and receive.

381
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:37,000
 And so we relate to God, trying to achieve, and it's exhausting,

382
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:42,000
 trying to be a good boy and a good girl.

383
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:46,000
 And when we try to do that, when we try to earn things with God or earn favor,

384
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:49,000
 man, it is so tiring.

385
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:52,000
 And we get depressed, we get anxious.

386
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:58,000
 And he's just, "Come. Rest. Receive."

387
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:05,000
 So, now, where does all of this leave us?

388
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:10,000
 We talked about where do we find satisfaction for our deepest longings.

389
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 What do we do?

390
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:16,000
 I said there are three ways that relate to Jesus that don't really work.

391
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:19,000
 The first one is we try to fit Jesus into our agenda,

392
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,000
 and we miss out on the relationship with him.

393
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,000
 The second one is we put our hope in things

394
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:27,000
 and believe that they can give us what only God can give us.

395
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:30,000
 And then the third one is we put our trust in ourselves.

396
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,000
 We think we can save ourselves.

397
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:34,000
 We can earn the right side, and it's just exhausting.

398
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:37,000
 It just leaves us tired.

399
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:40,000
 So, how do we receive what Jesus has to offer?

400
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:44,000
 Well, let me continue in the text, but I'm going to just summarize a little bit.

401
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:48,000
 So, he tells them to believe.

402
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:51,000
 They're like, "Well, if you want us to believe, then basically do another sign,

403
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:57,000
 like God did for Israel, or Moses did in the wilderness while we were wandering,

404
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,000
 and we got manna."

405
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:03,000
 In some sense, it's ridiculous because Jesus has actually just done

406
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,000
 the miracle of multiplying bread.

407
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:08,000
 Now they're asking for another sign in order to believe.

408
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:11,000
 Then Jesus, he responds this way, and in verse 32 he says this,

409
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:16,000
 "Very truly I tell you, it is not Moses who has given you the bread from heaven,

410
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:19,000
 but it is my Father who gives you the true bread from heaven.

411
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:23,000
 For the bread of God is the bread that comes down from heaven

412
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:26,000
 and gives life to the world."

413
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:29,000
 So, Jesus creates this contrast between manna and himself.

414
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:34,000
 Manna makes you hungry again.

415
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,000
 When you feed on me, you never hunger again.

416
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:41,000
 I am the true bread from heaven, and the true bread from heaven is not just for Israel,

417
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:44,000
 but it's for the world.

418
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,000
 And he gives it. He loves giving it.

419
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:50,000
 So, then in verse 34, "Some people in the crowd," not everyone,

420
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:53,000
 because if you read on past verse 35, that's where we're going to stop,

421
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:56,000
 you see that not everyone responds to the word "some."

422
00:25:56,000 --> 00:26:01,000
 They say, "Sir." They said, "Always give us this bread."

423
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:08,000
 Now what's interesting is that the word that's translated here as "Sir" is actually curious.

424
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:13,000
 And it means "Sir, Lord, Master."

425
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:17,000
 And there actually has been a shift in some of the people in the crowd,

426
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:22,000
 because earlier on they called Jesus "Rabbi," "Teacher."

427
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:27,000
 And now they call him "Lord."

428
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:32,000
 And I love this, because Jesus has been patiently engaging their questions,

429
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:35,000
 engaging how they're trying to relate to him,

430
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:41,000
 and keep trying to point him towards how to receive from him what he has to offer.

431
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:47,000
 And now a shift has occurred, where they went from seeing him as a teacher

432
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:50,000
 to seeing him as a Lord, and he says,

433
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:54,000
 "Give me, or always give us this bread. We want it."

434
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:57,000
 And they're doing essentially what Jesus asked them to do,

435
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:01,000
 which is to come and to receive and believe.

436
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:04,000
 And then we get to verse 35, where Jesus says,

437
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:10,000
 "I am the bread of life. Whoever comes to me will never go hungry,

438
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:14,000
 and whoever believes in me will never be thirsty.

439
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:17,000
 I am the one who fully satisfies.

440
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:22,000
 I am the one who fills that longing that nothing else fills."

441
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:28,000
 I am the one who can bring deep joy even as we walk through difficult things,

442
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:31,000
 where it doesn't even make sense that there's any joy in our lives.

443
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:35,000
 But it's because you have feasted on the bread of life,

444
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:39,000
 because you have come to Jesus.

445
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:43,000
 And so the remedy for our brokenness, our tiredness, and emptiness

446
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:46,000
 is found when we come to Jesus in faith.

447
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:54,000
 We commune with him, and our relationship with God is restored.

448
00:27:54,000 --> 00:28:01,000
 Now, a lot of times, we see this coming to Jesus

449
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:05,000
 and receiving what he has to offer.

450
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:14,000
 We see this as an ending, like finishing a race instead of a beginning.

451
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:18,000
 So when we see it as an ending, it's like, "Well, I've arrived.

452
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:21,000
 There's nothing else anymore for me to do.

453
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:24,000
 I received this bread. I received this life that Jesus has to give."

454
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,000
 And there's some truth to that.

455
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:28,000
 There is a shift.

456
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:33,000
 Even the Gospel of John talks about we cross over from death to life.

457
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:37,000
 Something spiritually has shifted. We are born again.

458
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:43,000
 But what Jesus invites us into is not just a finish line,

459
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:46,000
 but instead it's a beginning of a relationship with him

460
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:49,000
 where we commune with him.

461
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:53,000
 And as I was preparing for today, I really felt that God was saying

462
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:56,000
 he wants us to commune with him.

463
00:28:56,000 --> 00:29:01,000
 Because even if we're Christian, it doesn't always mean we're spending time with him.

464
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,000
 Think of me and my family.

465
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:07,000
 So I have my wife, Chris, and I have Ellie, my daughter.

466
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:10,000
 Now, we live in the same flat.

467
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:16,000
 But I, even though we live in the same flat, I could not spend time with them.

468
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:19,000
 I could just be doing my own thing.

469
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:23,000
 But if I do that, I actually miss out on the joy

470
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:28,000
 that is brought to me when I spend time with my wife and my daughter.

471
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:32,000
 Now, just this week, I'm very busy. I'm a man who has a lot going on.

472
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:37,000
 But I always try to make my family a priority and time with my daughter a priority.

473
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:42,000
 And so this Saturday, I had some time, was it Saturday or Friday?

474
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:44,000
 I played with my daughter.

475
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:47,000
 And she was chasing me, and then she wanted me to chase her.

476
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:51,000
 And I'm out of shape, so she's getting me tired, making me run around.

477
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:55,000
 Suddenly you have all these other kids who are joining in, they're chasing me.

478
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:58,000
 And then whenever I'm chasing Ellie, they're all chasing Ellie.

479
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:05,000
 And spending that time with my daughter just creates a deeper love,

480
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:11,000
 a deeper attachment to my daughter, a deeper joy.

481
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:18,000
 And in a similar way, when we actually commune with our Savior,

482
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:21,000
 it grows our love for Him.

483
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:26,000
 And these other lesser things that we're still often attached to,

484
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:31,000
 these things that we put our hope on, they become less important.

485
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:36,000
 Because we know who truly fulfills.

486
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,000
 They start fading more in the background.

487
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:43,000
 But right now, I think for many of us, and if we're just honest,

488
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:45,000
 that's not where we're at.

489
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:49,000
 We've crossed the line, some of us crossed the line,

490
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 or we've seen it as a finish line instead of a beginning of a relationship.

491
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:56,000
 And Jesus is saying, "Come to me, feast on me, commune with me.

492
00:30:56,000 --> 00:31:00,000
 I want you to experience the full satisfaction that is in me."

493
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:06,000
 The full contentment, the full joy that I have to offer.

494
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:11,000
 So you don't have to chase after these other things anymore.

495
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:17,000
 So I want to invite a worship team to come up.

496
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:24,000
 We're going to move into a time of celebrating communion.

497
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 Now, most of the time we do communion, we pass the bread and the wine around,

498
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:29,000
 but today we're going to do it different.

499
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:34,000
 We're actually going to celebrate communion by inviting you to come forward.

500
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:37,000
 And I want to do a little traffic flow here.

501
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,000
 So when we celebrate communion, wherever you're sitting,

502
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:44,000
 please go to the back and come forward this way, and then go to the sides.

503
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:47,000
 And you can come any time.

504
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:52,000
 You can take the bread and the wine any time.

505
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:56,000
 But I want to just say a few more things about that.

506
00:31:56,000 --> 00:32:05,000
 First, the bread symbolizes Jesus' body given for you, because he loves you.

507
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:11,000
 The cup of grape juice, it symbolizes Christ's blood poured out for you,

508
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:15,000
 for the forgiveness of your sins.

509
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 And Jesus is inviting us. He's saying, "I am the bread of life.

510
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:24,000
 Whoever comes to me will never go hungry,

511
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:28,000
 whoever believes in me will never be thirsty."

512
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:33,000
 And he's inviting us to come and to feast with him, to commune with him,

513
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:36,000
 to spend time with him, to receive from him.

514
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:39,000
 And we don't come because our life's cleaned up and we're perfect.

515
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:43,000
 We come because we need Jesus. We need his grace.

516
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:46,000
 And it's like when we come and we commune with him,

517
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:48,000
 and we receive what he has to offer, the grace,

518
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:53,000
 that's when our life changes.

519
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:57,000
 Now, as I've been talking, maybe something stood out to you

520
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:00,000
 as a way of relating to Jesus where we've been off.

521
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:03,000
 Maybe it's a talk we need to have with Jesus,

522
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:07,000
 "Jesus, I'm sorry that I'm angry when these things haven't worked out in my life.

523
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:09,000
 I see that I've made them idols."

524
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:15,000
 Or maybe it's just a deep gratitude of the work of Jesus in our lives.

525
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:18,000
 So I just want to encourage you to actually spend some time preparing,

526
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:25,000
 giving God thanks, maybe sorting something out in your hearts before you come.

527
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:30,000
 And if you're not yet a Christian, but you feel a tug in your heart,

528
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:35,000
 you can actually come and take communion as your expression

529
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:39,000
 that you want to begin a relationship with Jesus.

530
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:43,000
 So let me pray over us, and then we're going to have just some space

531
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:45,000
 where you can come forward.

532
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 But let me pray for us.

533
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 Jesus, I thank you so much that you are the bread of life.

534
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:58,000
 I thank you that you are the one who truly fills that void in our lives

535
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:04,000
 that can give us peace, that can satisfy our deep longings,

536
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 and in whom we can find peace and rest and stillness.

537
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:12,000
 And Jesus, you know our heart is wondering.

538
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:16,000
 We're all over the place, and we constantly look to other things.

539
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:20,000
 But I just pray that as we come that you just pour out your grace over us,

540
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:26,000
 that you reveal your love, and that as we commune with you,

541
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:30,000
 that all these other things, that they start fading away,

542
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:36,000
 that they become less significant because you are the bread of life.

543
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:41,000
 And so we thank you, we worship you, and we're just humbled

544
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:44,000
 and become empty-handed, but we come now to receive Jesus.

545
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:47,000
 I pray this in your name. Amen.

